[{"location":"index.html#FilesLH","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html#Comparing-and-Manipulating-Directories","page":"FilesLH","title":"Comparing and Manipulating Directories","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH","text":"clear_directory\nis_dir_empty\nmake_dir\nfind_common_base_dir\nfiles_in_dir\nfiles_not_in_dir2\ndir_diff_report","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.clear_directory","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.clear_directory","text":"clear_directory(tgDir; askFirst)\n\n\nClear a directory and its sub-directories\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.is_dir_empty","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.is_dir_empty","text":"is_dir_empty(d)\n\n\nIs a directory empty?\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.make_dir","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.make_dir","text":"make_dir(d)\n\n\nMake a directory for a full path.\n\ntest this +++++\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.find_common_base_dir","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.find_common_base_dir","text":"find_common_base_dir(pathV)\n\n\nFind common base directory for a set of absolute paths.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.files_in_dir","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.files_in_dir","text":"files_in_dir(d)\n\n\nMake a list of all files in a given directory. Recurses sub-directories. Each line is of the form \"subdir/file.ext\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.files_not_in_dir2","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.files_not_in_dir2","text":"files_not_in_dir2(dir1, dir2)\n\n\nMake a list of files that occur in dir1, but not in dir2. Recurses sub-directories. Only compares file names.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.dir_diff_report","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.dir_diff_report","text":"dir_diff_report(dir1, dir2; io)\n\n\nReport differences between two directories and their sub-directories. Based on file names only.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#Handling-File-Names","page":"FilesLH","title":"Handling File Names","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH","text":"add_extension\nchange_extension\nextensions_equal\nhas_extension\nfilesep\npaths_equal","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.add_extension","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.add_extension","text":"add_extension(filePath, newExt)\n\n\nAdd extension to a file, unless it already has one.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.change_extension","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.change_extension","text":"change_extension(filePath, newExt)\n\n\nChange or add extension to a path. newExt may or may not include the leading \".\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.extensions_equal","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.extensions_equal","text":"extensions_equal(f1, f2)\n\n\nAre two extensions equal, ignoring leading \".\"?\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.has_extension","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.has_extension","text":"has_extension(filePath)\n\n\nDoes file have an extension?\n\n\n\n\n\nhas_extension(filePath, fExt)\n\n\nDoes file have a particular extension? Ignoring leading '.'.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.filesep","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.filesep","text":"filesep()\n\n\nFile separator for current OS.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.paths_equal","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.paths_equal","text":"paths_equal(f1, f2)\n\n\nCompare two paths, taking into account that trailing file separators do not count.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#File-Transfer","page":"FilesLH","title":"File Transfer","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH","text":"rsync_command\nrsync_dir\nremote_copy\nmake_remote_dir\ngit_upload_dir","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.rsync_command","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.rsync_command","text":"rsync_command(srcDirIn, tgDirIn; trialRun, doDelete, doCompress, verbose, inclSubDirs, progress, excludeV)\n\n\nRsync to or from remote machine. Only for directories.\n\nFails if local or remote paths contain spaces.\n\nArguments\n\nsrcDirIn, tgDirIn :: String   Source and target directories.   Remote directory must include part required for ssh (e.g. lhendri@longleaf.unc.edu:)\ndoDelete :: Bool   Should orphan files be deleted on target? False by default.\ntrialRun :: Bool\nprogress :: Bool   Show progress indicator\n\n#ToDo: How to make the interpolation work when there are quotes around the objects?\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.remote_copy","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.remote_copy","text":"remote_copy(localPath, remotePath, sshStr, upDown; trialRun)\n\n\nCopy a file between local and remote computer using scp. scp replaces existing files without warning.\n\nSyntax\n\n`scp /path/local lhendri@longleaf.unc.edu:/path/remote`\n\nArguments\n\nsshStr :: String\n\ne.g. \"lhendri@longleaf.unc.edu\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.make_remote_dir","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.make_remote_dir","text":"make_remote_dir(remoteDir, sshStr; trialRun, createParents)\n\n\nMake a directory on the remote, optionally creating all parents as well. Creates a command of the form ssh lhendri@longleaf.unc.edu 'mkdir -p ~/home/abc'. Shows on-screen error if the directory already exists.\n\nGenerates on-screen output from ssh login.\n\nNote that other shell commands can be run with the same syntax.\n\nSee https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/8612/programmatically-creating-a-remote-directory-using-ssh\n\nArguments\n\nsshStr: e.g. \"lhendri@longleaf.unc.edu\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#FilesLH.git_upload_dir","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH.git_upload_dir","text":"git_upload_dir(repoDir; trialRun)\n\n\nUpload a repo to git.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html","page":"FilesLH","title":"FilesLH","text":"","category":"page"}]
